Exercise 2: Simple Calculator

Create a program that performs basic arithmetic operations.

# exercise2.py
"""
Task: Simple Calculator
1. Ask for two numbers
2. Perform addition, subtraction, multiplication, division
3. Display all results
"""

# Get input
num1 = float(input("Enter first number: "))
num2 = float(input("Enter second number: "))

# Calculate
addition = num1 + num2
subtraction = num1 - num2
multiplication = num1 * num2

# Handle division by zero
if num2 != 0:
    division = num1 / num2
else:
    division = "Undefined (division by zero)"

# Display results
print("\n" + "="*30)
print("       CALCULATOR RESULTS")
print("="*30)
print(f"{num1} + {num2} = {addition}")
print(f"{num1} - {num2} = {subtraction}")
print(f"{num1} * {num2} = {multiplication}")
print(f"{num1} / {num2} = {division}")
print("="*30)

Sample Run:


Enter first number: 15
Enter second number: 4

==============================
       CALCULATOR RESULTS
==============================
15.0 + 4.0 = 19.0
15.0 - 4.0 = 11.0
15.0 * 4.0 = 60.0
15.0 / 4.0 = 3.75
==============================

Exercise 3: Temperature Converter

Convert between Celsius and Fahrenheit.

# exercise3.py
"""
Task: Temperature Converter
1. Ask for temperature in Celsius
2. Convert to Fahrenheit
3. Display both
"""

celsius = float(input("Enter temperature in Celsius: "))

# Convert to Fahrenheit
fahrenheit = (celsius * 9/5) + 32

print(f"\n{celsius}Â°C = {fahrenheit}Â°F")

# Bonus: Add Kelvin conversion
kelvin = celsius + 273.15
print(f"{celsius}Â°C = {kelvin}K")

Sample Run:

Enter temperature in Celsius: 25

25.0Â°C = 77.0Â°F
25.0Â°C = 298.15K

Exercise 4: Age in Different Units

Calculate age in months, weeks, days.

# exercise4.py
"""
Task: Age Calculator
1. Ask for age in years
2. Calculate in months, weeks, days
3. Display all
"""

years = int(input("Enter your age in years: "))

months = years * 12
weeks = years * 52
days = years * 365
hours = days * 24
minutes = hours * 60

print(f"\nAge: {years} years")
print("="*30)
print(f"Months:   {months:,} months")
print(f"Weeks:    {weeks:,} weeks")
print(f"Days:     {days:,} days")
print(f"Hours:    {hours:,} hours")
print(f"Minutes:  {minutes:,} minutes")
print("="*30)

Sample Run:


Enter your age in years: 25

Age: 25 years
==============================
Months:   300 months
Weeks:    1,300 weeks
Days:     9,125 days
Hours:    219,000 hours
Minutes:  13,140,000 minutes
==============================

Exercise 5: Simple Interest Calculator

Calculate simple interest.

# exercise5.py
"""
Task: Simple Interest Calculator
Formula: SI = (P * R * T) / 100
P = Principal, R = Rate, T = Time
"""

print("SIMPLE INTEREST CALCULATOR")
print("="*30)

principal = float(input("Enter principal amount: $"))
rate = float(input("Enter interest rate (% per year): "))
time = float(input("Enter time (years): "))

# Calculate interest
interest = (principal * rate * time) / 100
total_amount = principal + interest

print("\n" + "="*30)
print("RESULTS")
print("="*30)
print(f"Principal:   ${principal:,.2f}")
print(f"Rate:        {rate}%")
print(f"Time:        {time} years")
print(f"Interest:    ${interest:,.2f}")
print(f"Total:       ${total_amount:,.2f}")
print("="*30)

Sample Run:
SIMPLE INTEREST CALCULATOR
==============================
Enter principal amount: $1000
Enter interest rate (% per year): 5
Enter time (years): 3

==============================
RESULTS
==============================
Principal:   $1,000.00
Rate:        5.0%
Time:        3.0 years
Interest:    $150.00
Total:       $1,150.00
==============================

1.10 Weekly Project: Interactive Story Generator
Create a program that generates a custom story based on user input.

# week1_project.py
"""
WEEK 1 PROJECT: Interactive Story Generator
Create a unique story using user inputs
"""

print("="*50)
print("        INTERACTIVE STORY GENERATOR")
print("="*50)

# Get user inputs
print("\nLet's create your story! Answer these questions:")
name = input("Enter a character name: ")
age = input("Enter their age: ")
city = input("Enter a city name: ")
superpower = input("Enter a superpower: ")
animal = input("Enter an animal: ")
color = input("Enter a color: ")
food = input("Enter a favorite food: ")
number = input("Enter a number: ")

# Convert age to integer for calculations
age_num = int(age)

# Generate story parts
print("\n" + "="*50)
print("           YOUR CUSTOM STORY")
print("="*50)

# Story template with variations based on age
if age_num < 18:
    print(f"\nOnce upon a time, in the magical city of {city}, there lived a young")
    print(f"hero named {name}. At just {age} years old, {name} discovered they had")
    print(f"the incredible power of {superpower}!")
    
else:
    print(f"\nIn the bustling metropolis of {city}, {name} lived an ordinary life")
    print(f"as a {age}-year-old professional. But everything changed when they")
    print(f"unlocked their hidden ability: {superpower}!")

# Common story elements
print(f"\nOne day, while eating their favorite {color} {food}, {name} noticed")
print(f"a mysterious {animal} acting strangely. The {animal} seemed to be")
print(f"carrying a message that would change everything...")

print(f"\nUsing their {superpower} for the first time, {name} discovered")
print(f"that they weren't alone. There were {number} other heroes in {city},")
print(f"each with their own unique powers!")

print(f"\nTogether, they formed a team to protect the city from evil.")
print(f"And so began the legend of {name}, the hero with the power of")
print(f"{superpower}, defender of {city}!")

print("\n" + "="*50)
print("            THE END")
print("="*50)

# Bonus: Save story to file
save = input("\nDo you want to save your story? (yes/no): ")
if save.lower() == 'yes':
    filename = f"{name}_story.txt"
    with open(filename, 'w') as file:
        file.write("INTERACTIVE STORY\n")
        file.write("="*50 + "\n")
        file.write(f"Character: {name}\n")
        file.write(f"Age: {age}\n")
        file.write(f"City: {city}\n")
        file.write(f"Superpower: {superpower}\n")
        file.write("="*50 + "\n\n")
        file.write("[Story content would be saved here]")
    print(f"Story saved as '{filename}'")

Sample Run:


==================================================
        INTERACTIVE STORY GENERATOR
==================================================

Let's create your story! Answer these questions:
Enter a character name: Alex
Enter their age: 25
Enter a city name: Tokyo
Enter a superpower: teleportation
Enter an animal: dragon
Enter a color: purple
Enter a favorite food: ramen
Enter a number: 7

==================================================
           YOUR CUSTOM STORY
==================================================

In the bustling metropolis of Tokyo, Alex lived an ordinary life
as a 25-year-old professional. But everything changed when they
unlocked their hidden ability: teleportation!

One day, while eating their favorite purple ramen, Alex noticed
a mysterious dragon acting strangely. The dragon seemed to be
carrying a message that would change everything...

Using their teleportation for the first time, Alex discovered
that they weren't alone. There were 7 other heroes in Tokyo,
each with their own unique powers!

Together, they formed a team to protect the city from evil.
And so began the legend of Alex, the hero with the power of
teleportation, defender of Tokyo!

==================================================
            THE END
==================================================

Do you want to save your story? (yes/no): yes
Story saved as 'Alex_story.txt'

