Common Errors to Avoid:

# 1. Forgetting to convert input
age = input("Age: ")
next_year = age + 1  # ERROR! age is string

# Correct:
age = int(input("Age: "))
next_year = age + 1

# 2. Division by zero
result = 10 / 0  # ZeroDivisionError

# 3. Mismatched types
result = "10" + 5  # TypeError

# 4. Undefined variables
print(x)  # NameError if x not defined

